Factor $32x^3-4x^2+20x$.
inference:
Solution:
First, factor out the greatest common factor of the three terms, which is $4x$.
$$\begin{align*} 32x^3-4x^2+20x&=4x(8x^2-x+5)\\ &=4x(2x-5)(4x^2+10x+25)\\ &=\boxed{4x(2x-5)(4x^2+10x+25)}. \end{align*}$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{4x(2x-5)(4x^2+10x+25)}$. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: We see that the largest common factor of the coefficients is $4$ and that $x^1$ is the largest power of $x$ which divides all the terms, so we can factor out $4x$ and get $$\boxed{4x(8x^2-x+5)}.$$
